cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.DM, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with the problem of determining the flip distance between two triangulations of a simple polygon, which is a problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the analysis of the complexity of the problem, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also mentions the problem of determining the rotation distance between two binary trees, which falls under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
